Now I have a clear understanding of the bug and the code. Let me analyze the key issue:

In `registerAgentImplementation`, when an agent implementation is disposed (the cleanup handler in `toDisposable`), it sets:

```typescript
if (entry.data.isDefault) {
    this._hasDefaultAgent.set(Iterable.some(this._agents.values(), agent => agent.data.isDefault));
}
```

The problem is that `Iterable.some(this._agents.values(), agent => agent.data.isDefault)` checks `agent.data.isDefault` which is a static property on the agent data – it doesn't check whether the agent has an active implementation (`agent.impl`). So even after the Copilot extension is disabled and its implementation is removed, this check still returns `true` because the agent data still exists in the map with `isDefault: true`.


This leaves `_hasDefaultAgent` (which controls `ChatContextKeys.enabled`) stuck at `true` even after the implementation disappears, keeping all the gated commands visible. The fix is straightforward: I need to also verify that the agent has an active implementation by checking `!!agent.impl` alongside the `isDefault` flag. That's just a single-line modification to the condition in `chatAgents.ts`. Let me verify this against the recent git history to make sure I'm on the right track.

